Key Responsibilities:

Responsible for the corporate communication strategies and implementation of ad hoc projects, event organization, road show, online platforms management, graphic design, translation, etc. to promote the corporate image and client relationship
Promote the reputation of the UK universities under management
Overall in charge of the global recruitment, selection and admission of the undergraduate students for the three universities in UK
Participation in other projects as assigned  

Minimum Requirements:

Degree holder in communications, journalism, translation, arts, design or related discipline or above;
At least 1 year relevant working experience in investor relations or corporate communication; knowledge of the social and financial business in Hong Kong, China and UK; sound understanding in school operation in UK an advantage;
Skillful in graphic design, photographing a must;
Excellent in spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua) ; proficient English writing, translation and proof-reading skills;
Innovative, a good team player and able to work independently, eager to learn, self-motivated, independent and willing to take new challenges, occasional business travel may be required

Qualified applicants please send your CV together with current and expected salary for the application. All information gathered will be handled in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment purpose only.
